Producer price inflation jumped to a four-month high in July, lifted by food products, beverages and tobacco products. The producer price index (PPI) accelerated to 1.9% in July from 0.5% previously. Month on month  it had increased 1.2%. The median estimate according to a Bloomberg forecast was for PPI to have increased to 1.3% year on year. Food products, beverages and tobacco products rose by 3.2% year on year, and transport equipment by 8.3%. The monthly figure was driven by coke, petroleum, chemical, rubber and plastic products, which rose by 4.8%. mjoo@businesslive.co.za